.TH "hash_messagepad" 9 "hash_messagepad" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hash_messagepad \- Pads a message and write the nblw bits.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hash_messagepad
.BI "(struct hash_device_data *device_data "  ","
.BI "const u32 *message "  ","
.BI "u8 index_bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device_data" 12
Structure for the hash device.
.IP "message" 12
Last word of a message.
.IP "index_bytes" 12
The number of bytes in the last message.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function manages the final part of the digest calculation, when less
than 512 bits (64 bytes) remain in message. This means index_bytes < 64.
